 null, it might lead to an exception being thrown. I'm wondering if there's a public API for registering duplicate resources that could throw the error. If it involves duplicate bytes, then malformed classes could cause complications. I need to consider if loading a malformed class with loadClass is supported. However, asserting broken behavior seems unsupported, so I should focus on normal public APIs and avoid duplicating class definitions.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Creating dedicated test classes**\\n\\nI’m looking at the existing TestClassMakerTest, which targets the outer class but not the Loader. The developer suggests that I keep coverage for each dynamic-access class in its own dedicated test file, with a one-to-one mapping under src/test/java. There's an active class named TestClassMakerInnerLoaderTest.java that needs renaming. I also think about creating a dedicated test for the Loader, but the documentation warns that the functions aren’t thread-safe, which could affect a concurrent test design.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_BaZCnNVF6aXlutOFimAT5VHO|fc_0bea5f8df0a30683016a23fef8b2848196b3179b92fe9da344", "name": "read", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/io.quarkus.gizmo/gizmo2/2.2.0/build.gradle"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1847, "output": 886, "cacheRead": 17920, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 20653, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1780743907642, "responseId": "resp_0bea5f8df0a30683016a23fee41000819680cb3f3047aa293d"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_BaZCnNVF6aXlutOFimAT5VHO|fc_0bea5f8df0a30683016a23fef8b2848196b3179b92fe9da344", "toolName": "read", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativec